ng constructs like 'inside' or 'unique' ensures compliance.\n*   The reset logic is implemented synchronously as required: `if (reset) current_state <= STATE_A; else current_state <= next_state;` (I will adjust the provided testbench reset logic to match the strict requirement of active-high synchronous reset, as the testbench used `negedge reset` which implies asynchronous reset, but the spec requested synchronous active-high reset).\n\n**Refinement on Reset**: The specification requires a *synchronous active high* reset. The sequential block will be: `if (reset) current_state <= STATE_A; else current_state <= next_state;`\n\n*Self-Correction during implementation*: The provided testbench used `always @(posedge clk or negedge reset)` which is asynchronous reset. I must correct this to only use `always @(posedge clk)` and implement the synchronous reset as specified.",
